{"id": "duc04-testb-15:17#51", "contents": "Matthew Shepard, a 21-year-old gay college student, died on Monday, five days after he was found unconscious on a Wyoming ranch where he had been left tied to a fence for 18 hours in near-freezing temperatures. The attack on Shepard, a freshman at the University of Wyoming, sparked nationwide outrage and vigils, with people turning out to honor him from Denver to the University of Maryland. The incident has also fueled debates over hate-crimes legislation in Western states, including Wyoming, which has resisted such laws."}
